Johannesburg Mayor Geoff Makhubo returns to the State Capture Inquiry, to discuss money flows during his time as treasurer of the ANC in the city. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Mayor, Geoff Makhubo, appears before the State Capture Commission of Inquiry on Monday. Makhubo is been implicated in questionable payments from IT company EOH. The company is alleged to have made payments to several senior ANC members including Makhubo and Zizi Kodwa. READ:Â Herman Mashaba calls out Joburg mayor Geoff Makhubo Makhubo was the Johannesburg ANC's Treasurer-General and Finance MMC when the payments were made. Geoffrey Makhubo's evidence will focus on donations that EOH Africa made to the ANC. The Commission has previously heard of allegations of Makhubo irregularly receiving payments from EOH Africa through his service providing company named Molwewane Consulting.